us (rapper)|Lazarus]], physician and rapper from [[Detroit]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pakhiphop.com/2009/06/mc-lazarus-rapper-and-docter.html |title=Welcome to Pakistans Hip Hop Music Scene: MC Lazarus, Rapper and Doctor |publisher=Pakhiphop.com |date=June 9, 2009 |accessdate=October 26, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110321090856/http://www.pakhiphop.com/2009/06/mc-lazarus-rapper-and-docter.html |archive-date=March 21, 2011 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n[[File:Lazarus (rapper).jpeg|thumb|Kamran Rashid Khan, also known as Lazarus, is a graduate of [[Wayne State University]].]]\n*[[Kamran Pasha]] \u2013 Hollywood screenwriter and director; wrote the Showtime hit series ''[[Sleeper Cell (TV miniseries)|Sleeper Cell]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kamranpasha.com/kamran_pasha.php |title=Kamran Pasha, Author of Mother of the Believers |publisher=Kamranpasha.com |accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Kumail Nanjiani]] \u2013 actor and [[comedian]], ''[[Franklin & Bash]]''\n*[[Lubna Agha]] \u2013 artist\n*[[Mehr Hassan]] \u2013 Indian father, Pakistani mother; actress, model and classical dancer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1689887/|title=Mehr Hassan|work=IMDb|accessdate=December 14, 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Mehreen Jabbar]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mehreenjabbar.com/ |title=Filmmaker |publisher=Mehreen Jabbar |accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref> \u2013 director of ''[[Ramchand Pakistani]]''\n*[[Minhal Baig]] - film director\n*[[Munaf Rayani]] \u2013 guitarist for the [[Texas|Texan]] post-rock band [[Explosions in the Sky]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rectangular.org/explosions/EITS_Interview_Tokion_45_Jan2005.htm |title=Interview with Munaf in Tokion magazine no. 45, 2005 |publisher=Rectangular.org |accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Munni Begum]] \u2013 born Nadira; ghazal singer from Pakistan; based in [[Chicago, Illinois]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.muziqpakistan.com/songs.php?auth=54 |title=songs and music on |publisher=Muziqpakistan.com |accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Muqeem Khan]] \u2013 first Pakistani in the [[Hollywood]] VFX industry, 1996<ref name=TEDTalk>{{cite web|url=http://talentsearch.ted.com/video/Muqeem-Khan-Playful-technology|title=TED2013 Talent Search|accessdate=December 14, 2015}}</ref><ref name=BrightFuture>{{cite web|url=http://www.muqeemkhan.com/BrightFuture.html|title=Untitled Document|accessdate=December 14, 2015}}</ref><ref name=Blending>[http://www.muqeemkhan.com/press/Qatar_Tribune_Nation_page_23.pdf'' \u2022 \u201cBlending Real With Virtual\u201d, Qatar Tribune, Doha, Qatar, May, 2009.'']</ref><ref name=Digital>[http://www.thenews.com.pk/TodaysPrintDetail.aspx?ID=159280&Cat=4&dt=1/24/2009'' \u2022 \u201cDigital age in Pakistan not a distant dream\u201d, The News, Karachi, Pakistan, January, 2011.'']</ref><ref name=Final-Fantasy>[https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/246683/Final-Fantasy-the-Spirits-Within/credits'' \u2022 Final-Fantasy-the-Spirits-Within - Cast, Crew, Director and Awards - NYTimes.com. (n.d.). Retrieved September 11, 2013, from http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/246683/Final-Fantasy-the-Spirits-Within/credits'']</ref><ref name=Total>[http://www.muqeemkhan.com/press/Total%20Realism%20Penunsula%202013.pdf ''\u2022 \u201cTotal realism with computer graphics no distant dream\u201d, Qatar Tribune, Doha, Qatar, March, 2013.'', February 25, 2013]</ref><ref name=anim2>{{cite web|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/110559/animation-in-pakistani-feature-films/|title=Animation in Pakistani feature films|date=January 28, 2011|work=The Express Tribune|accessdate=December 14, 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]] \u2013 [[Grammy]]-nominated singer-songwriter and former frontwoman of [[iiO (dance group)|iiO]]; known for the song \"[[Rapture (iiO song)|Rapture]]\"; one of the prominent vocalists of [[electronic dance music]]; has collaborated with DJs [[Armin van Buuren]], [[John Creamer & Stephane K]] and [[BT (musician)|BT]]\n* [[