ot Javed Ahmed | date=May 20, 2009}}</ref> a [[FTSE 250]] company which is one of Britain's oldest brands<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/business/5388020.stm Sweet success for oldest brand]  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090204123803/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/business/5388020.stm |date=February 4, 2009 }}</ref>\n* [[Farooq Kathwari]] \u2013 Chairman, President and Chief Executive officer of [[Ethan Allen (furniture company)|Ethan Allen]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/money/companies/2007-06-25-ceo-profile-kathwari_N.htm|title=CEO Profile: Ethan Allen's Kathwari was always a leader - USATODAY.com|accessdate=December 14, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Syed Moiz Balkhi]]  \u2013  Florida-based entrepreneur; founder of WPBeginner<ref name=\"SpannagleSoward2010\">{{cite book|last1=Spannagle|first1=Peter|last2=Soward|first2=Sarah|title=WordPress and Flash 10x Cookbook|year=2010|publisher=[[Packt|Packt Publishing Ltd]]|isbn=9781847198839|page=387|quote=WPBeginner: site to help beginners learn about WordPress, by Syed Balkhi.}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Chowdry]] (1955\u20132001) \u2013 [[Forbes 400]] businessman; founder of air cargo company [[Atlas Air]], which in 2001 was worth over $1.39&nbsp;billion<ref>{{cite news|author=Betsy Schiffman, January 25, 2001, 12:00&nbsp;pm ET |url=https://www.forbes.com/2001/01/25/0125faces.html |title=Forbes Faces: Michael Chowdry |work=Forbes |date= January 25, 2001|accessdate=October 26, 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Tariq Farid]] \u2013 entrepreneur; owner and CEO of [[Edible Arrangements]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tariqfarid.com/2009/02/about-tariq-farid.html |title=About |publisher=Tariq Farid |accessdate=October 26, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101024192127/http://www.tariqfarid.com/2009/02/about-tariq-farid.html |archivedate=October 24, 2010 }}</ref>\n*[[Nabeel Gareeb]] \u2013  appointed President and Chief Executive Officer and a member of the Board of Directors of [[MEMC Electronic 