a/article545843.ece|archivedate=December 14, 2008|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n*[[Hasan Minhaj]] \u2013 comedian, [[The Daily Show|Daily Show]] correspondent<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/11/business/media/hasan-minhaj-correspondents-dinner.html|title=Comedian Hasan Minhaj to Perform at White House Correspondents' Association Dinner|work=The New York Times|date=11 April 2017|accessdate=12 April 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Preacher Moss]] \u2013 standup comedian, comedy writer<ref name=AMMF/>\n*[[Zahra Noorbakhsh]] \u2013 comedian, writer, actor, co-host of #GoodMuslimBadMuslim podcast\n*[[Kumail Nanjiani]] \u2013 standup comedian, actor<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2017/05/08/kumail-nanjianis-culture-clash-comedy|title=Kumail Nanjiani's Culture-Clash Comedy|publisher=The New Yorker|date=May 8, 2017|accessdate=October 14, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Dean Obeidallah]] \u2013 standup comedian<ref name=PBS/>\n*[[Azhar Usman]] \u2013 standup comedian<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/religion/religions/islam/people/azharusman.shtml Azhar Usman] BBC \u2013 Religion and Ethics (BBC). Retrieved on 2009-06-18. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090521230050/http://www.bbc.co.uk/religion/religions/islam/people/azharusman.shtml |date=May 21, 2009 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.americaabroadmedia.org/programs/view/id/28 \"America's Funniest Muslim\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090425154549/http://www.americaabroadmedia.org/programs/view/id/28 |date=April 25, 2009 }} America Abroad Media. Retrieved on 2009-06-18.</ref>\n*[[Maysoon Zayid]] \u2013 standup comedian, actress<ref name=PBS/>\n\n==Crime==\n*[[United States v. Hasan K. Akbar|Hasan Akbar]] \u2013 convicted of premeditated murder in a grenade attack on fellow soldiers<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/7667169 |title=Soldier gets death for killing officers |publisher=NBC News |date=2005-04-29 |accessdate=2012-12-15}}</ref>\n*[[Hesham Mohamed Hadayet]] \u2013 Egyptian-American w