]] \u2013 Muslim scholar<ref name=\"2004-PRESS-RELEASES\">{{cite press release| title=Dr.Omar Khalidi Visited Ufa and Chelyabinsk and Discussed Muslim Life in America| publisher=yekaterinburg.usconsulate.gov| date=April 18, 2004| accessdate=August 25, 2011| url=http://yekaterinburg.usconsulate.gov/pr-04182004.html| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005083126/http://yekaterinburg.usconsulate.gov/pr-04182004.html| archivedate=October 5, 2011| df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/2010/khalid-rememberance.html| title=Remembering Omar Khalidi| date=December 10, 2010| accessdate=August 27, 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Amir Hussain (religious scholar)|Amir Hussain]] \u2013 Muslim scholar, editor of the ''[[Journal of the American Academy of Religion]]''\n\n==Science==\n*[[Shereef Elnahal]] \u2013 commissioner, [[New Jersey Department of Health]], transitioning to [[CEO]] of [[University Hospital (Newark, New Jersey)|University Hospital]], [[Newark, New Jersey|Newark]] in July 2019\n*[[Fazlur Khan]] \u2013 structural engineer (designed the [[Sears Tower]], [[John Hancock Center]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fazlurrkhan.com/ |title=Fazlur Rahman Khan |publisher=Fazlurrkhan.com |date= |accessdate=2012-12-15}}</ref>\n*[[Ayub K. Ommaya]] \u2013 neurosurgeon, inventor of the [[Ommaya reservoir]]<ref>{{cite journal |author=Geoff Watts |url=http://www.lancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(08)61642-6/fulltext |title=Ayub Khan Ommaya |journal=The Lancet |date=November 1, 2008 |volume=372 |issue=9549 |page=1540 |accessdate=2012-12-15 |doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(08)61642-6}}</ref>\n*[[Ahmed Zewail]] \u2013 [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize winner in Chemistry]], 1999 for his work on [[femtochemistry]]<ref>{{cite journal |author=Ahmed Zewail |url=http://www.zewail.caltech.edu/ |title=Prof. Ahmed Zewail Website at Caltech |journal=Chemical Physics |volume=366 |issue=1\u20133 |pages=2\u20138 |doi=10.1016/j.chemphys.2009.07.01