dia commentator, and author of the book ''Scapegoats: How Islamophobia Helps Our Enemies & Threatens Our Freedoms''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/05/12/islam-twitter_n_860726.html#s277449&title=Arsalan_Iftikhar_AKA |title=Islam On Twitter |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date= |accessdate=2014-02-19}}</ref>\n*[[Queen Noor of Jordan|Noor Al-Hussein]] \u2013 anti-[[nuclear weapons proliferation]] advocate and former [[Queen consort of Jordan]]\n*[[Hakim Jamal]] \u2013 civil rights activist; Member of the [[Nation of Islam]] but converted to traditional Islam after the assassination of his cousin Malcolm X.\n*[[Zalmay Khalilzad]] \u2013 former [[United States Ambassador to the United Nations|US Ambassador to the United Nations]]; former [[United States Ambassador to Iraq|U.S. Ambassador to Iraq]] and [[United States Ambassador to Afghanistan|Afghanistan]]<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/middle_east/4736394.stm | work=BBC News | title=Zalmay Khalilzad: US power broker | date=2007-01-08 | accessdate=2010-05-08}}</ref>\n*[[Yuri Kochiyama]] \u2013 [[Japanese American]] [[activist]] who converted to [[Sunni Islam]] from [[Protestantism]] in 1971{{sfn|Fujino|2005|p=206}}\n*[[Umar Lee]] \u2013 Activist and Writer\n*[[Edina Lekovic]] \u2013 Communications Director of the [[Muslim Public Affairs Council]]<ref>[http://frum.nationalreview.com/post/?q=YzBmOGRlNjJjMmJlZGEyNjJiNWFkZWMyY2E1Mjk1OTY= National Review Online] Retrieved on 2009-06-18.  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061206131018/http://frum.nationalreview.com/post/?q=YzBmOGRlNjJjMmJlZGEyNjJiNWFkZWMyY2E1Mjk1OTY%3D |date=December 6, 2006 }}</ref>\n*[[Gholam Mujtaba]]  \u2013  chair of the Pakistan Policy Institute, a think tank dedicated to improve the US-Pakistan relationship\n*[[Ilhan Omar]] \u2013 One of the first two Muslim women elected to Congress.<ref name=omar-tlaib>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/hannahallam/rashida-tlaib-ilhan-omar-muslim-congress|title=Rashida Tlaib And Ilhan Omar Are The First Muslim Women Elected To Congress|publisher=BuzzFeed News|date=November 6, 2018|accessdate=November 6, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Farah Pandith]] \u2013 Special Representative to Muslim Communities for the US Department of State; official advisor to President Obama on Muslim matters\n*[[Zainab Salbi]] \u2013 co-founder and president for [[Women for Women International]] \n*[[Betty Shabazz]] (also known as Betty X) \u2013 civil rights activist and educator; widow of Malcolm X<ref>[http://www.gale.cengage.com/free_resources/bhm/bio/shabazz_b.htm \"Betty Shabazz\"] Gale Ceneage Learning</ref>\n*[[Ilyasah Shabazz]] \u2013 social activist and daughter of Malcolm X\n*[[Malcolm Shabazz]] \u2013 activist and grandson of Malcolm X; [[Malcolm_Shabazz#Death|Murdered]] during a labor rights tour in [[Mexico]]\n*[[Malcolm X|el-Hajj Malik el-Shabazz]] (also known as Malcolm X) \u2013 human rights activist, civil rights activist, public speaker and [[Nation of Islam|Black Muslim]] minister;<ref>''The Last Speeches''. Bruce Perry, ed. New York: Pathfinder Press (1989). p. 261.</ref> Joined the Nation of Islam in 1952, before converting to Sunni Islam in 1964.\n*[[Azadeh Shahshahani]] \u2013 human rights attorney and past president of the [[National Lawyers Guild]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.counterpunch.org/2016/05/31/from-tehran-to-atlanta-social-justice-lawyer-azadeh-shahshahanis-fight-for-human-rights/ |title=From Tehran to Atlanta: Social Justice Lawyer Azadeh Shahshahani's Fight for Human Rights |publisher=Counterpunch F|date=2016-05-31}}</ref>\n* [[Saghir \"Saggy\" Tahir]] \u2013 [[New Hampshire]] State Representative; the only elected Pakistani American in the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]];<ref name=\"BBC-2004\">{{cite news|title=US Muslims flex political muscle| author=Barnie Choudhury |publisher=BBC |date= January 23, 2004| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/americas/3422685.stm}} Retrieved December