ary-clinton-pays-rich-tribute-to-muslim-us-army-captain/\n| url-status              = live\n| newspaper             = The Express Tribune\n| language              = English\n| location              = [[Karachi]], [[Pakistan]]\n| publisher             = [[Lakson Group]]\n| archive-url           = https://web.archive.org/web/20160821104559/http://tribune.com.pk/story/1013648/hillary-clinton-pays-rich-tribute-to-muslim-us-army-captain/\n| archive-date          = 2016-08-21\n| access-date           = 2016-08-23\n}}</ref>\n\n===Foreign military service===\n* [[Ma Dunjing (1910\u20132003)|Ma Dunjing]] \u2013 [[Islam in China|Chinese Muslim]] General of the [[National Revolutionary Army]], immigrated to Los Angeles in the United States after retirement in 1950\n* [[Ma Hongkui]] \u2013 [[Islam in China|Chinese Muslim]] General of the [[National Revolutionary Army]], immigrated to Los Angeles in the United States after retirement in 1950\n\n==Art==\n[[File:Viennale talk (2), Shirin Neshat.jpg|thumb|upright|Artist [[Shirin Neshat]] at the [[Vienna International Film Festival|Viennale 2009]]]]\n*[[Kameelah Janan Rasheed]] \u2014 Artist based in [[New York City]]\n*[[Deana Haggag]] \u2013 Egyptian-American art museum curator, President and CEO of [[United States Artists]] in Chicago\n*[[Shirin Neshat]] \u2013 Iranian-American visual artist and film director. Awarded [[The Dorothy and Lillian Gish Prize]] in 2006, and the [[Silver Lion]] in 2009<ref>Joy Dietrich, [https://tmagazine.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/05/14/asked-and-answered-shirin-neshat/ \"Asked and Answered\"] Shirin Neshat, ''The New York Times'', May 14, 2010. Accessed June 6, 2011</ref>\n*[[Shahzia Sikander]] \u2013 Pakistani-American artist and [[MacArthur Fellows Program|MacArthur Fellow]]<ref>[http://www.absolutearts.com/artsnews/2004/03/29/31920.html Indepth Arts News: \"Shahzia Sikander: Flip Flop\"], Absolute Arts. Accessed June 6, 2011</ref><ref>Ian Berry, [http://www.ifa.de/ausstellungen/dt/programmrueckblick/2006/zeitspruenge-raumfolgen/interview-shahzia-sikander/ \"Nemesis\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928055457/http://www.ifa.de/ausstellungen/dt/programmrueckblick/2006/zeitspruenge-raumfolgen/interview-shahzia-sikander/ |date=September 28, 2011 }}, ifa-Galerien. Accessed June 6, 2011</ref>\n\n==Business==\n[[File:Mohamed A. El-Erian at the World Economic Forum Summit on the Global Agenda 2008.jpg|thumb|upright|[[PIMCO]] CEO [[Mohamed El-Erian]] at the [[World Economic Forum]]]]\n*[[Mohamed A. El-Erian]] \u2013 CEO of [[PIMCO]], manager of over $1 trillion in global assets<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/04/15/business/muslims-on-wall-street-bridging-two-traditions.html?pagewanted=3 | title=Muslims on Wall Street, Bridging Two Traditions | author=Kevin Roose | date=April 14, 2012 | newspaper=[[The New York Times]] | accessdate=April 15, 2012 | page=3 | quote=Mohamed A. El-Erian, chief executive of the giant bond house Pimco and one of the highest-ranking Muslims in American finance}}</ref>\n* [[Fuad El-Hibri]] \u2013 CEO of [[Emergent BioSolutions]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/money/2004-05-18-muslim-ceos_x.htm |title=Muslim CEOs of U.S. firms fight terrorism, 'stop evil' |work=USA Today | first1=Del |last1=Jones |date=2004-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://people.forbes.com/profile/fuad-el-hibri/29177 |title=Fuad El-Hibri |work=Forbes |access-date=September 3, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510020551/http://people.forbes.com/profile/fuad-el-hibri/29177 |archive-date=May 10, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*[[Shahid Khan]] \u2013 owner of the [[Jacksonville Jaguars]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL), the English [[Premier League]] team [[Fulham F.C.]], and automobile parts manufacturer [[Flex-N-Gate]] in [[Urbana, Illinois]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sunshineslate.com/2011/12/05/fanning-the-flames-new-jacksonville-jaguars-owners-muslim-faith-stirs-stupidity/ |accessdate