rich]] for their mechanistic studies of DNA repair<ref>{{cite source |author=Broad, William J. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/08/science/tomas-lindahl-paul-modrich-aziz-sancarn-nobel-chemistry.html/|accessdate=2020-01-20 |url-status=alive|date=January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Sports==\n\n===Boxing===\n[[File:Anderson ali.jpg|thumb|upright|Boxer [[Muhammad Ali]] in 1978]]\n*[[Muhammad Ali]] \u2013 became a member of the [[Nation of Islam]] in 1964,<ref>[http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/organizations/n/nation_of_islam/index.html Nation of Islam] ''The New York Times''. Retrieved on 2009-04-23.</ref> converted to [[Sunni Islam]] in 1975<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2008-05-20|url=http://www.beliefnet.com/Faiths/Islam/2005/02/Muhammad-Alis-New-Spiritual-Quest.aspx|title=Muhammad Ali's New Spiritual Quest|publisher=[[Beliefnet]]|author=Caldwell, Deborah}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gale.com/free_resources/bhm/bio/ali_m.htm |title=Free Resources \u2013 Black History \u2013 Biographies \u2013 Muhammad Ali |publisher=Gale |date= |accessdate=2012-12-15}}</ref>\n*[[Bernard Hopkins]] \u2013 former [[Middleweight]] and [[Light Heavyweight]] [[world champion]]<ref>Steve Bunce (2001-11-11) [https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2001/nov/11/boxing.news The forgotten prince] ''The Guardian''. Retrieved on 2009-06-18.</ref>\n*[[Eddie Mustafa Muhammad]] \u2013 former [[Light Heavyweight]] Champion\n*[[Matthew Saad Muhammad]] \u2013 former [[Light Heavyweight]] Champion<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxrec.com/media/index.php/Matthew_Saad_Muhammad |title=Matthew Saad Muhammad \u2013 Boxrec Boxing Encyclopaedia |publisher=Boxrec.com |date=2012-01-12 |accessdate=2012-12-15}}</ref>\n*[[Dwight Muhammad Qawi]] \u2013 former [[Light Heavyweight]] and [[Cruiserweight (boxing)|Cruiserweight]] Champion<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxrec.com/media/index.php/Dwight_Muhammad_Qawi |title=Dwight Muhammad Qawi \u2013 Boxrec Boxing Encyclopaedia |publisher=Boxrec.com |date=2012-01-10 |a